    "Closure-carrying replay fixture (Patch C / plan §9 'TLA replay determinism fix').",
    "",
    "Demonstrates the determinism contract: a recorded WorkerResponse carries",
    "`local_closure_results` and `local_closure_revalidation` payloads inline so",
    "replay never re-invokes `run_local_closure_axioms`. The probe is I/O-",
    "dependent (lake-spawned Lean script with timeouts and transport jitter)",
    "and re-probing during replay would break byte-for-byte determinism.",
    "",
    "When recording a fixture from a live run, the runtime CLI is expected to",
    "gate payload capture on the env var `TRELLIS_RECORD_CLOSURE_PAYLOADS=1`",
    "and persist the captured payloads alongside the WorkerResponse fields.",
    "Replay never sets this var.",
    "",
    "Why this fixture's test is `#[ignore]`d: byte-equality with engine output",
    "requires Patch C-B's accept-time bookkeeping to be fully landed AND its",
    "TODO_PATCH_C_D_* hash placeholders to stabilize. Until then this file",
    "documents the wire format only — flip the ignore off when C-B is stable",
    "and the placeholders match the engine's deterministic output."
